<h2>Blowers</h2>
<p><a href="https://wikileaks.org/">Wikileaks</a> and <a href="https://www.facebook.com/openleaks">Openleaks</a> are influential in today's world. Each individual has to decide whether these leakers' contributions are positive or negative. It is increasingly difficult to regulate what is said on the web. Leak releases and the ongoing debate about super-injunctions show this to be the case. But, with the internet entering a new stage of development, for example, Microsoft buys up Skype, governments are looking at how best, or even whether, to regulate the internet, (as discussed at the May 2011 e-G8 Summit in Paris).</p>